wt - Git worktree management for parallel AI agent workflows

Usage: wt [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  config  Manage configuration and shell integration
  step    Run individual operations
  hook    Run configured hooks
  select  Interactive worktree selector
  list    List worktrees and their status
  switch  Switch to a worktree
  remove  Remove worktree; delete branch if merged
  merge   Merge worktree into target branch

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version

Global Options:
  -C <path>
          Working directory for this command

      --config <path>
          User config file path

  -v, --verbose
          Show commands and debug info

Getting started

  wt switch --create feature    Create worktree and branch
  wt switch feature             Switch to existing worktree
  wt list                       Show all worktrees
  wt merge                      Squash, rebase, and merge to default branch

Run `wt config shell` to set up directory switching.

Docs: https://worktrunk.dev
GitHub: https://github.com/max-sixty/worktrunk


